<%
  set_meta_tags(
    title: "Getting Started - Rails UI Components",
    description: "Learn how to install, use, and customize Rails UI components in your projects.",
    keywords: "Rails, UI, Components, Installation, Usage, Getting Started"
  )
%>
<% breadcrumb :ui_getting_started %>

<article class="space-y-8">
  <header class="space-y-4">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">Getting Started</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
      Learn how to install, use, and customize Rails UI components in your projects.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Requirements</h2>

    <div class="p-6 rounded-lg bg-gray-50">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 font-semibold text-gray-900">Backend</h3>
          <ul class="text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>Ruby</strong> 3.2.3+</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>Rails</strong> 7.0.8+</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>ViewComponent</strong> gem</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 font-semibold text-gray-900">Frontend</h3>
          <ul class="text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>Node.js</strong> 18+</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>TailwindCSS</strong> 4.0</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>Vite</strong> for asset compilation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Installation</h2>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">1. Add Required Gems</h3>
        <p class="mb-3 text-gray-600">Add these dependencies to your <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">Gemfile</code>:</p>

        <div class="p-4 overflow-x-auto text-gray-100 bg-gray-900 rounded-lg">
          <pre><code># Gemfile
gem 'view_component'
gem 'vite_rails'
gem 'turbo-rails'
gem 'pagy', '~> 9.3.4'</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">2. Install Dependencies</h3>

        <div class="p-4 overflow-x-auto text-gray-100 bg-gray-900 rounded-lg">
          <pre><code># Install Ruby gems
bundle install

# Install frontend dependencies
yarn install</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">3. Copy Components</h3>
        <p class="mb-3 text-gray-600">Copy the components you need from this template to your Rails project:</p>

        <div class="p-4 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            üìÅ Copy entire <code>app/components/ui/</code> folder or individual component folders to your project.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">4. Start Development</h3>

        <div class="p-4 overflow-x-auto text-gray-100 bg-gray-900 rounded-lg">
          <pre><code># Start Rails server
bin/rails server

# Start Vite dev server (in another terminal)
yarn dev
# or
bin/vite dev</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Component Structure</h2>

    <p class="text-gray-600">Each component follows a consistent pattern:</p>

    <div class="p-4 overflow-x-auto text-gray-100 bg-gray-900 rounded-lg">
      <pre><code>app/components/ui/[component_name]/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ component.rb          # Main component class
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ component.html.erb    # Template (when needed)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ component.css         # Component-specific styles
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ component_controller.js # Stimulus controller (when needed)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ [nested_components]/  # Sub-components</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-blue-50">
      <p class="text-sm text-blue-800">
        <strong>üí° Tip:</strong> All components inherit from <code>ApplicationComponent</code> and are namespaced under <code>Ui::</code>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Basic Usage</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Simple Component</h3>
        <p class="mb-3 text-gray-600">Most components can be used with minimal configuration:</p>

        <div class="p-4 overflow-x-auto text-gray-100 bg-gray-900 rounded-lg">
          <pre><code>&lt;%= render Ui::Btn::Component.new(variant: :primary) do %&gt;
  Click me!
&lt;% end %&gt;</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Component with Options</h3>
        <p class="mb-3 text-gray-600">Components accept various options for customization:</p>

        <div class="p-4 overflow-x-auto text-gray-100 bg-gray-900 rounded-lg">
          <pre><code>&lt;%= render Ui::Alert::Component.new(
  type: :success,
  title: "Success!",
  icon_path: "images/icons/check.svg"
) do %&gt;
  Your changes have been saved successfully.
&lt;% end %&gt;</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Complex Component</h3>
        <p class="mb-3 text-gray-600">Some components have nested sub-components:</p>

        <div class="p-4 overflow-x-auto text-gray-100 bg-gray-900 rounded-lg">
          <pre><code>&lt;%= render Ui::Card::Component.new do |card| %&gt;
  &lt;% card.with_header(title: "Card Title") %&gt;
  &lt;% card.with_body do %&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Card content goes here&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;% end %&gt;
  &lt;% card.with_footer do %&gt;
    &lt;%= render Ui::Btn::Component.new(variant: :primary) { "Action" } %&gt;
  &lt;% end %&gt;
&lt;% end %&gt;</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Customization</h2>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Modifying Styles</h3>
        <p class="mb-3 text-gray-600">You can customize component appearance in several ways:</p>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-gray-50">
            <h4 class="mb-2 font-medium text-gray-900">1. CSS Classes (Quick)</h4>
            <div class="p-3 overflow-x-auto text-sm text-gray-100 bg-gray-900 rounded">
              <pre><code>&lt;%= render Ui::Btn::Component.new(class: "bg-purple-600") do %&gt;
  Purple Button
&lt;% end %&gt;</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-gray-50">
            <h4 class="mb-2 font-medium text-gray-900">2. Component CSS (Recommended)</h4>
            <p class="mb-2 text-sm text-gray-600">Edit the component's CSS file:</p>
            <div class="p-3 overflow-x-auto text-sm text-gray-100 bg-gray-900 rounded">
              <pre><code>/* app/components/ui/btn/btn.css */
.btn--custom {
  @apply bg-purple-600 text-white hover:bg-purple-700;
}</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-gray-50">
            <h4 class="mb-2 font-medium text-gray-900">3. New Variants</h4>
            <p class="mb-2 text-sm text-gray-600">Add new variants to the component:</p>
            <div class="p-3 overflow-x-auto text-sm text-gray-100 bg-gray-900 rounded">
              <pre><code># app/components/ui/btn/component.rb
def initialize(variant: :primary, **options)
  @variant = variant # :primary, :secondary, :custom
  @options = options
end</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Development Commands</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-gray-50">
        <h3 class="mb-3 font-semibold text-gray-900">Development</h3>
        <div class="text-sm space-y-2">
          <div><code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">yarn dev</code> - Start Vite dev server</div>
          <div><code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">bin/rails server</code> - Start Rails server</div>
          <div><code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">bin/rails console</code> - Rails console</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-gray-50">
        <h3 class="mb-3 font-semibold text-gray-900">Production</h3>
        <div class="text-sm space-y-2">
          <div><code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">yarn build</code> - Build assets</div>
          <div><code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">yarn standard</code> - JavaScript linting</div>
          <div><code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">bundle exec rubocop</code> - Ruby linting</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">What's Next?</h2>

    <div class="p-6 rounded-lg bg-blue-50">
      <p class="mb-4 text-blue-800">Now that you have the basics, explore individual components in the sidebar to see detailed examples and learn about their specific options and usage patterns.</p>

      <p class="text-blue-700">
        Don't forget to check out <%= link_to "Good to know", ui_good_to_know_path, class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 font-medium underline" %> for architectural insights and best practices.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</article>
